x4freetext: Neutrons were produced by bombarding a T-Ti
target with 440 and 990 keV deuterons. The neutron
energy was selected by the angular position of the
sample with respect to the deuteron beam axis.
Polycrystalline powder of spectrally pure natural Ge
packed after weighting into plexiglass containers.

following quantities:

Subents 002 - 008)
peak-background separation abundance of

Ge(Li) efficiency                          3%
gamma-ray attenuation                      2%
contribution of interfer. reactions  =<10%
sample weight                          < 1%
